SpNote.note:
This library contains photometric standard stars for use with UFTI.
Each observation is already setup with the correct co-ordinates and the correct exposure times. All you need to do is to copy them to your science program.
Where noted in the title you should make sure you have already taken data which generates a flat field. This is because the stars are too bright and hence there is insufficient sky signal to make a flat. The data reduction recipe requires the flat to be pre-generated.
Also note that in the expectation that a full JHK set will be done repeat darks have been removed from the K exposures. If you are observing K only, then you will need to add a dark.
